  "prompt": "How do I write a good recommendation for an internship?",
  "response": "To write a good recommendation for an internship, follow these tips:\n\n1. Introduction\n- State your relationship to the candidate\n- Explain how long you've known them\n- Specify in what capacity you know them\n\n2. Highlight specific skills and qualities\n- Discuss the candidate's strengths\n- Provide concrete examples of their abilities\n- Focus on skills relevant to the internship\n\n3. Academic and professional achievements\n- Mention academic performance\n- Discuss notable projects or accomplishments\n- Describe leadership experiences\n\n4. Personal characteristics\n- Describe work ethic\n- Highlight interpersonal skills\n- Demonstrate reliability and motivation\n\n5. Specific examples\n- Use specific anecdotes that illustrate their capabilities\n- Provide context for their achievements\n- Show how they've demonstrated key competencies\n\n6. Comparative assessment\n- Compare them to peers or colleagues\n- Indicate their potential for growth\n- Express confidence in their abilities\n\n7. Closing\n- Offer strong endorsement\n- Provide contact information\n- State willingness to provide further details\n\n8. General writing tips\n- Be concise and clear\n- Use professional language\n- Proofread carefully\n- Print on official letterhead if possible\n\nTailor the recommendation to the specific internship requirements and emphasize relevant qualities.",
